('ANGOSTURA', 'Angostura trifoliata', 'Bonplandia trifoliata Willd., Galipea officinalis Hancock; Cusparia febrifuga Humb.\r\nex DC., Cusparia trifoliata (Willd.) Engl.', 'Antipyretic (f; HHB); Aperitif (1; EFS; FNF); Bitter (1; HHB; PH2);\r\nCarminative (f; EFS); Emetic (1; PH2); Gastrotonic (f; PH2); Laxative (f; PH2); Stimulant (f; EFS);\r\nStomachic (f; EFS); Tonic (f; PH2).', 'Anorexia (1; EFS; FNF); Diarrhea (f; PH2); Dysentery (f; HHB);\r\nDyspepsia (f; HHB); Fever (f; HHB; PH2); Gas (f; EFS); Hypoacidity (1; HHB).', '0.5 g (HHB).', 'Not covered (AHP).\r\nâ€œHazards and/or side effects not known for proper therapeutic dosagesâ€ (PH2) (but PH2\r\ndesignates no specific quantified dosage! JAD). Larger doses may induce nausea, vomiting, or\r\nboth (PH2).', 44, '', ''),
