\r\n9 of the treated patients improved cf 1 in the placebo controls. The insignificant reduction in pain\r\nwas confined to those whose pain did not radiate to one or both legs. â€œThere was a notable absence\r\nof identifiable clinical, hematological, or biochemical side effectsâ€ (PHM3:1). None of these authors\r\ncommented on the presence of 3 COX-2 inhibitors as well, kaempferol, oleanolic acid, and ursolic\r\nacid.', 326, '', ''),
